OL,6,F"I know this will be a worrying
OL,7,Fdevelopment for patients and families
OL,8,Fwho rely on CQC assessments when
OL,9,Fmaking choices about their care.
OL,11,F"I want to reassure them that I am
OL,12,Fdetermined to grip this crisis and
OL,13,Fgive people the confidence that the
OL,14,Fcare they're receiving has been
OL,15,Fassessed. This government will never
OL,16,Fturn a blind eye to failure."
